Our value prop is simple and based on Web3 principles. We would love to have more engaged like minded people to help us develop curriculum. Also passionate students about Web3
Hi guys, i‘m the founder of the break stuff app. We want to connect the physical sports card world with the digital (nft) world. Happy to connect & answer questions! 😎

@Kash I'd love to understand how you plan build a reputation as a viable education option? Many of the existing intuitions have years of legacy to attract students and some of the new outfits have backers like Peter Thiel to excite newcomers.
@schneida How do you plan on connecting the physical and digital world of cards? Can you prove authenticity of collectables?

In our app enviroment users can scan their physical cards and get an instant AI grading, which means our algo checks different industry standards and norms (centering, corners, edges, surface, colours) and presents the results as a note between 1-10.

Nft usecase 1 starts immediately afer that scenario where the user can decide if he wants to create a nft out of it:

https://youtu.be/MbIcVuHFj1Y

The utility of this nft is then to „digitally upgrade“ the card for the own collection, for showcasing on social or to help with selling on the marketplace and get a better ROI out of it. After a sale or a certain period of time the nft expires and has to be re-newed (▶️ pushes grading subscriptions)

Nft usecase 2 is more traditional one to work with clubs, athletes and associations to release unique nft trading card series with their off licenses.

An authentification will be possible at some point when we have built up a database of cards which is non existent in the sports world right now. There‘s one open source for Magic but thats it.
